nodes.documentation:
@title ChronoBank Asset Proxy.
 * Proxy implements ERC20 interface and acts as a gateway to a single platform asset.
Proxy adds symbol and caller(sender) when forwarding requests to platform.
Every request that is made by caller first sent to the specific asset implementation
contract, which then calls back to be forwarded onto platform.
 * Calls flow: Caller ->
            Proxy.func(...) ->
            Asset.__func(..., Caller.address) ->
            Proxy.__func(..., Caller.address) ->
            Platform.proxyFunc(..., symbol, Caller.address)
 * Asset implementation contract is mutable, but each user have an option to stick with
old implementation, through explicit decision made in timely manner, if he doesn't agree
with new rules.
Each user have a possibility to upgrade to latest asset contract implementation, without the
possibility to rollback.
 * Note: all the non constant functions return false instead of throwing in case if state change
didn't happen yet.
nodes.name: ChronoBankAssetProxy
init

nodes.documentation: Only platform is allowed to call.
nodes.name: onlyChronoBankPlatform

nodes.documentation: Only current asset owner is allowed to call.
nodes.name: onlyAssetOwner

nodes.documentation:
Returns asset implementation contract for current caller.
     * @return asset implementation contract.
nodes.name: _getAsset

nodes.documentation:
Returns asset total supply.
     * @return asset total supply.
nodes.name: totalSupply

nodes.documentation:
Returns asset balance for a particular holder.
     * @param _owner holder address.
     * @return holder balance.
nodes.name: balanceOf

nodes.documentation:
Returns asset allowance from one holder to another.
     * @param _from holder that allowed spending.
@param _spender holder that is allowed to spend.
     * @return holder to spender allowance.
nodes.name: allowance

nodes.documentation:
Returns asset decimals.
     * @return asset decimals.
nodes.name: decimals

nodes.documentation:
Transfers asset balance from the caller to specified receiver.
     * @param _to holder address to give to.
@param _value amount to transfer.
     * @return success.
nodes.name: transfer
transferWithReference

nodes.documentation:
Resolves asset implementation contract for the caller and forwards there arguments along with
the caller address.
     * @return success.
nodes.name: _transferWithReference
__transferWithReference
transferFrom
__transferFromWithReference

nodes.documentation:
Sets asset spending allowance for a specified spender.
     * @param _spender holder address to set allowance to.
@param _value amount to allow.
     * @return success.
nodes.name: approve
__approve

nodes.documentation:
Emits ERC20 Transfer event on this contract.
     * Can only be, and, called by assigned platform when asset transfer happens.
nodes.name: emitTransfer

nodes.documentation:
Emits ERC20 Approval event on this contract.
     * Can only be, and, called by assigned platform when asset allowance set happens.
nodes.name: emitApprove

nodes.documentation:
Resolves asset implementation contract for the caller and forwards there transaction data,
along with the value. This allows for proxy interface growth.
Indicates an upgrade freeze-time start, and the next asset implementation contract.
nodes.name: UpgradeProposal

nodes.documentation: Only asset implementation contract assigned to sender is allowed to call.
nodes.name: onlyAccess

nodes.documentation:
Returns asset implementation contract address assigned to sender.
     * @param _sender sender address.
     * @return asset implementation contract address.
nodes.name: getVersionFor

nodes.documentation:
Returns current asset implementation contract address.
     * @return asset implementation contract address.
nodes.name: getLatestVersion

nodes.documentation:
Returns proposed next asset implementation contract address.
     * @return asset implementation contract address.
nodes.name: getPendingVersion

nodes.documentation:
Returns upgrade freeze-time start.
     * @return freeze-time start.
nodes.name: getPendingVersionTimestamp

nodes.documentation:
Propose next asset implementation contract address.
     * Can only be called by current asset owner.
     * Note: freeze-time should not be applied for the initial setup.
     * @param _newVersion asset implementation contract address.
     * @return success.
nodes.name: proposeUpgrade

nodes.documentation:
Cancel the pending upgrade process.
     * Can only be called by current asset owner.
     * @return success.
nodes.name: purgeUpgrade

nodes.documentation:
Finalize an upgrade process setting new asset implementation contract address.
     * Can only be called after an upgrade freeze-time.
     * @return success.
nodes.name: commitUpgrade

nodes.documentation:
Disagree with proposed upgrade, and stick with current asset implementation
until further explicit agreement to upgrade.
     * @return success.
nodes.name: optOut

nodes.documentation:
Implicitly agree to upgrade to current and future asset implementation upgrades,
until further explicit disagreement.
     * @return success.
nodes.name: optIn
